.Dd June 3, 2025
.Dt UNSHARE 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm unshare
.Nd run a program in new namespaces
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl hV
.Op Fl u | -uts Oo = Pa file Oc
.Op Ar program Op Ar args ...
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
utility creates new namespaces, as specified by the options, and then
executes the specified program.  If
.Ar program
is not given, then the progrem specified in the environment variable
.Ev SHELL
(default
.Pa /bin/sh )
is run.
.Pp
The following options are available:
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Fl h
Display the help message and exit.
.It Fl V
Display the program version and exit.
.\" XXX formatting
.It Fl u , -uts Oo = Pa file Oc
Create a new UTS namespace.
If
.Pa file
is specified, the namespace is made persistent by creating a bind mount at
.Pa file .
Specifying
.Pa file
currently has no effect on
.Nx .
.Ss Namespaces
The following types of namspaces can be created with
.Nm :
.Bl -ohang
.It "UTS namespace"
.\"XXX more precise phrasing
Setting hostname or domainname will only affect the rest of the system.
.El
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
The following variable is referenced by
.Nm :
.Bl -hang
.It SHELL
If set, the string specified by
.Ev SHELL
is interpreted as the name of the shell to exec.
If the variable
.Ev SHELL
is not set,
.Pa /bin/sh
is used.
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Ex -std
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr unshare 2 ,
.Xr namespaces 7
.Sh HISTORY
The
.Nm
utility appeared in
.Nx 11 .
